"5:119:24" : {s: 5, a: 119, w: 24, r: "عظم", t: "ٱلْعَظِيمُ", l: "عَظِيم", lc: 120, tl: "l-ʿaẓīmu", lb: "প্রচন্ড",e: "(the) great", b: "মহান", f: 16, rm: "great, important, big, regard, honour, mighty, glorious, a man of moment, All-mighty, All-glorious, grievous, bounty/abounding, magnify/increase. azzama - to make great."},
"5:120:1" : {s: 5, a: 120, w: 1, r: "اله", t: "لِلَّهِ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "lillahi", lb: "আল্লাহ ",e: "To Allah (belongs)", b: "আল্লাহর জন্য/উদ্দেশ্যে", f: 102, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
